            . I am shopman to John Lloyd, <rs id="t18220522-60-viclabel329" type="occupation">linen draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220522-60-victim542 t18220522-60-viclabel329"></join>. On the 6th of May in consequence of information, I went out, and overtook the prisoner, and found a piece of print in his apron, which belonged to Mr. Lloyd; the ready money price would be 39 s. 6 d. I had seen it safe half an hour before, in the passage by the door.</p>
               <p>
            
